f y8f ff6 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">o<span class="ff7"> <span class="_ _a8"> </span><span class="ff3 ws1">and so on. </span></span></div><div class="t m0 x1d h4 y90 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws4">Varying electromagnetic energy of the wave in sum with varying </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y91 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws3">internal energy of the air in medium 1 satisfy the law of energy </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y92 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws7">conservation.  The conditions of this law compliance are also </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y93 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws2">conditions of the wave&apos;s existence.   </div><div class="t m0 x1d h4 y94 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 wsf">Further we shall show that quantitative estimates confirm the </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y95 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws15">assumption of depolarization, first, as a source of induction in the </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y12 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws54">magnetic wave, and, second – as a mechanism of the heat energy </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y96 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws2">transformation into the magnetic energy of the wave.  </div><div class="t m0 x1d h4 y97 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m0 x1d h16 yff ff4 fs0 fc1 sc0 ls2 ws0">9. Quantitative Estimates </div><div class="t m0 x1d h4 y332 ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws20">It was shown above that the change of internal energy of medium 1 <span class="_ _8"></span> </div><div class="t m0 x9 h4 y3be ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 wsc">with temperature change by </div><div class="c x2a y2b7 w8 h17"><div class="t m0 x2d h13 yad ff1 fs10 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">T</div></div><div class="c x5f y2b7 w6 h17"><div class="t m0 x2d h25 yad ffb fs10 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">Δ</div></div><div class="t m0 xb h16 y3be ff3 fs3 fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0"> is determined by (6.2) for <span class="_ _cd"> </span><span class="ff2 fsa">1</span></div><div class="c x63 y120 w4 h17"><div class="t m0 x2d h2a yad ffb fsa fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">=</div></div><div class="c x67 y120 w14 h17"><div class="t m0 x2d h16 yad ff1 fsa fc1 sc0 ls0 ws0">s</di